    • Method Detail

      • beforeExpressionPush

        protected void beforeExpressionPush(DfaValue value,
                                    PsiExpression expression,
                                    TextRange range,
                                    DfaMemoryState state)
        Called before a PsiExpression result is being pushed to the memory state stack during symbolic interpretation. The result of single expression can be pushed many times to the different memory states.
        Parameters:
        value - a value being pushed
        expression - a physical PsiExpression which evaluates to given value.
        range - if not-null, specifies a part of expression which corresponds to the value (like "a ^ b" range in "a ^ b ^ c" expression).
        state - a memory state where expression is about to be pushed

      • beforeMethodReferenceResultPush

        protected void beforeMethodReferenceResultPush(DfaValue value,
                                               PsiMethodReferenceExpression methodRef,
                                               DfaMemoryState state)
        Called before a result of method reference execution is being pushed to the memory state stack during symbolic interpretation. It's not guaranteed that this method is called for every reachable non-void method reference. However if it's called for some method reference, then all possible values will be passed here.
        Parameters:
        value - result of method reference execution
        methodRef - a method reference
        state - a memory state

      • checkReturnValue

        protected void checkReturnValue(DfaValue value,
                                PsiExpression expression,
                                PsiParameterListOwner context,
                                DfaMemoryState state)
        Called for every expression which corresponds to the method or lambda result.
        Parameters:
        value - expression value
        expression - an expression which produces given value. For conditional return like return cond ? ifTrue : ifFalse; this method will be called for ifTrue and ifFalse separately.
        context - a method or lambda which result is being returned
        state - a memory state
